# Shared Skills

This repository's canonical skills live in `.agents/skills`. Cursor compatibility symlinks are available under `.cursor/skills`, and Claude Code compatibility symlinks are available under `.claude/skills`.

Before starting a task that matches one of these workflows, read the relevant `SKILL.md`:

- Understanding how the toolkit works end-to-end, where to start, the overall workflow/structure, what to do next, or which dependencies a step needs (orientation / how-to guide): `.agents/skills/ask-me-anything/SKILL.md`
- Finding, discovering, or filtering matching job postings (by role, keywords, location, recency, or visa sponsorship): `.agents/skills/job-search/SKILL.md`
- Resume tailoring, JD analysis, ATS optimization, rendered resume output: `.agents/skills/resume-writer/SKILL.md`
- Application status, pipeline health, notes, and metadata updates: `.agents/skills/application-tracker/SKILL.md`
- Behavioral interview prep, STAR story banks, and company-specific behavioral coaching: `.agents/skills/behavioral-interview-prep/SKILL.md`
- Researching a company and role for interviews (product, size, teams, values, stage, comp, WLB, ratings, visa) and building a question bank under `interviews/company-specific/<company>/company-info/`: `.agents/skills/company-research/SKILL.md`
- Periodic memory hygiene (expire stale discoveries, prune search-log rows, flag stale/duplicate LESSONS, verify links, measure the pipeline funnel — dry-run by default, moves not deletes): `.agents/skills/gardener/SKILL.md`

The list above enumerates only the PUBLIC skills that ship in this toolkit repo. The private `coding-interview` skill is not routed here — it is registered separately by an overlay-shipped, git-ignored `.cursor/rules/private-skills.mdc` that is present only when the private overlay is mounted.

Edit skill content only in `.agents/skills`; do not replace compatibility symlinks with copied files.
